# <%ModuleName%>

<%Description%>

## Quick start

```powershell
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd <%ModuleName%>
./build/bootstrap.ps1
Invoke-Build -File ./build/module.build.ps1
```

## Project layout

```
<%ModuleName%>/
├── src/<%ModuleName%>/        Module source
│   ├── <%ModuleName%>.psd1    Manifest (runtime deps only)
│   ├── <%ModuleName%>.psm1    Entry point
│   ├── Public/                Exported functions
│   └── Private/               Internal helpers
├── build/
│   ├── module.build.ps1       InvokeBuild task graph
│   ├── bootstrap.ps1          Dependency installer
│   └── build.requires.psd1    Pinned tool versions (ModuleFast)
├── tests/
│   ├── unit/                  Pester 5 unit tests
│   └── integration/           Post-build artifact tests
└── docs/                      Generated help (platyPS)
```

## Build tasks

| Task              | Description                                            |
|-------------------|--------------------------------------------------------|
| `.` (default)     | Clean → Validate → Lint → Test → Docs → Package       |
| `Lint`            | PSScriptAnalyzer with project settings                 |
| `Test`            | Pester 5 unit tests + code coverage                    |
| `IntegrationTest` | Post-build artifact validation                         |
| `Docs`            | platyPS markdown and XML help generation               |
| `Package`         | Stage module + create archive                          |
| `Release`         | Full pipeline + publish to PSGallery                   |

## Adding a command

1. Create `src/<%ModuleName%>/Public/Verb-Noun.ps1`
2. Add the function name to `FunctionsToExport` in the manifest
3. Create `tests/unit/Verb-Noun.Tests.ps1`
4. Run `Invoke-Build -File ./build/module.build.ps1 -Task Lint, Test`

